'''El Hossein El Ouardi''' ({{lang-ar|الحسين الوردي}} - born 22 September 1954) is a Moroccan politician of the [[Party of Progress and Socialism]]. Since 3 January 2012, he holds the position of Minister of Health in [[Abdelilah Benkirane]]'s government.<ref name=mad>{{cite web|title=Official bio |url=http://www.maroc.ma/NR/rdonlyres/7D5D90D6-DE23-474F-95DD-36D170D284E6/0/BioElHosseinElOuardi.pdf |publisher=Government of Morocco |accessdate=15 June 2012 }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Jihane Gattioui|title=El Hossein El Ouardi tente de redresser les dysfonctionnements|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/lematin/164564|accessdate=16 June 2012|newspaper=Le Matin|date=2012-03-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/liberation/24879|title=Le SNSP reçu par Hossein El Ouardi : Vers la tenue d'un colloque national sur la santé|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/albayane/11516|title=Passation de pouvoirs entre Yasmina Badou et El Hossein El Ouardi : "Garantir et faciliter l'accès des citoyens aux prestations de santé"|access-date=2016-07-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Farida Moha|title=Entretien avec le ministre de la Santé , El Hossein El Ouardi|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/lematin/163960|accessdate=16 June 2012|newspaper=Le Matin|date=2012-03-15}}</ref>
In January 2014, El Ouardi was physically assaulted while exiting the parliament in Rabat. His assailants were members of the pharmacists union/lobby, and one of them was the brother-in-law of [[Fouad Ali El Himma]], the influential advisor and close-friend of [[Mohammed VI]], in addition to being the cousin of the [[Party of Authenticity and Modernity]] female Mayor of [[Marrakesh]].<ref>{{cite news|title=لماذا لم يطرد حزب البام إلياس العماري بتهمة تحريض الصيادلة|newspaper=الأسبوع|date=16 January 2014}}</ref> The incident resulted in minor injuries for the minister.
