{{Infobox park | name = Naypyidaw Water Fountain Garden | alt_name = {{my|နေပြည်တော် ရေပန်း ဥယျာဉ်}} | photo = Naypyidaw -- Water Fountain Garden.JPG | photo_width = | photo_caption = The front gate | type = [[Urban park]] | location = [[Naypyidaw]] | coords = | area = {{convert|165|acre|km2}} | created = 2008 | operator = | visitation_num = | status = Open all year }}
The '''Naypyidaw Water Fountain Garden''' ({{lang-my|နေပြည်တော် ရေပန်း ဥယျာဉ်}}) is a garden in [[Naypyidaw]], [[Myanmar]]. The {{convert|165|acre|ha|sing=on}} garden is situated near the [[Naypyidaw City Hall]] with a steel structure arch-way. Also included in the garden are a main pond with three fountains and 11 small ponds with 13 different fountains, a {{convert|30|ft|m|sing=on}} high clock tower, nine recreation centres, two small gardens, two stone gardens and ten feet wide buggy road and footpaths. The garden was set up near the [[Naypyidaw-Taungnyo Road]].
