{{Infobox body of water |name = Nelaug |native_name = |native_name_lang = |other_name = |image = |caption = |image_bathymetry = |alt_bathymetry = |caption_bathymetry = |pushpin_map = Aust-Agder#Norway |pushpin_label_position = bottom |pushpin_map_caption = Location of the lake |coordinates = {{coord|58|40|16|N|08|34|10|E|region:NO_type:waterbody|display=inline,title}} |location = [[Froland]] and [[Åmli]] |type = [[Reservoir]] |inflow = [[Nidelva (Aust-Agder)|Nidelva]] |outflow = [[Nidelva (Aust-Agder)|Nidelva]] |catchment = |basin_countries = [[Norway]] |date-built = |date-flooded = |length = {{convert|8|km}} |width = {{convert|3|km}} |area = {{convert|10|km2|abbr=on}} |depth = |max-depth = |volume = |residence_time = |shore = {{convert|68|km}} |elevation = {{convert|138|m}} |frozen = |islands = |cities = |reference = [[Norwegian Water Resources and Energy Directorate|NVE]] }}
'''Nelaug''' is a [[lake]] in the municipalities of [[Froland]] and [[Åmli]] in [[Aust-Agder]] county, [[Norway]]. The {{convert|10|km}} lake is formed by a [[dam]] which regulates a [[hydroelectricity|hydroelectric]] power plant on the [[Nidelva (Aust-Agder)|Nidelva]] river. The village of [[Nelaug]] is located near the dam in [[Froland]] municipality. The lake is located about {{convert|11|km}} south of the village of [[Åmli (village)|Åmli]], about {{convert|15|km}} southeast of the village of [[Dølemo]], and about {{convert|20|km}} north of [[Blakstad, Aust-Agder|Blakstad]].<ref name="snl">{{cite encyclopedia|url=https://snl.no/Nelaug_-_innsj%C3%B8|title=Nelaug – innsjø|editor-first=Geir|editor-last=Thorsnæs|accessdate=2017-12-09|date=2015-07-15|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|publisher=[[Kunnskapsforlaget]]|language=Norwegian}}</ref>
==Name== The [[Old Norse]] form of the name must have been ''Niðlaug''. The first element ''Nið'' is the old name of the river [[Nidelva (Aust-Agder)|Nidelva]] and the last element is ''laug'' which means "lake".<ref name="snl" />
